<SUMMARY>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=2 -->
SUMMARY:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 This document proposes the adoption of a new airworthiness directive (AD) that is applicable to certain Boeing Model
747 series airplanes. This proposal would require inspections of the inboard and outboard strut chords, stiffeners,
and web to detect cracks and loose fasteners; repair of the chords, stiffeners, or web, if necessary; and replacement
of any loose fastener. This proposal is prompted by reports of fatigue cracks and loose fasteners found in the forward
lower spar web of the inboard strut on Model 747 series airplanes equipped with Pratt &amp; Whitney JT9D&hyph;3 and
JT9D&hyph;7 series engines. The actions specified by the proposed AD are intended to prevent separation of the strut
from the wing of the airplane due to fatigue cracking.
