<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(xi) Federal Medical Care Recovery Act, 42 U.S.C. 2651&hyph;53. (See subpart M.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Claims against nonappropriated fund activities and the risk management program (RIMP). (See subpart L.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Claims under industrial security regulations (DOD Directive (DODD) 5220.6) and claims by the U.S. Postal Service
for losses or shortages in postal accounts caused by unbonded Army personnel (39 U.S.C 411 and DOD Manual 4525.6&hyph;M).
(See DA Pam 27&hyph;162, chap 5, sec XI.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) DA Pam 27&hyph;162, chapter 8 lists other laws and regulations under which claims not covered by this regulation
may be cognizable. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Where a conflict exists between a general provision of this part and a specific provision found in subparts implementing
