<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(16) Take initial action on claims arising in emergency situations as outlined in &sect;536.15(c). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(17) Provide assistance as available or take appropriate action to ensure that command claims services and area claims
offices are carrying out their responsibilities as set forth in paragraphs (c) and (d) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(18) Serve as proponent for Claims Legal Automated Information Management System (CLAIMS) and provide standard
automated claims data management programs for use worldwide. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(19) Ensure proper training of claims personnel. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(20) Coordinate claims activities with the Air Force, Navy, Marine Corps, and other DOD agencies to ensure a consistent
DOD claims program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(21) Supervise the investigation and processing of medical malpractice claims arising in Army medical centers within
the United States. Provide medical claims JAs, medical claims attorneys and medical claims investigators assigned
to such medical centers with technical guidance and direction on such claims. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(22) Coordinate support with the Office of The Surgeon General on matters relating to medical malpractice claims.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(23) Issue an accounting classification to all properly designated claims settlement and approval authorities.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(24) Perform the investigation, processing, and settlement of claims arising in areas not within the areas of operation
of command claims services unless specifically delegated to a SJA of a command or designee. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Chiefs of command claims services. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Chiefs of command claims services will_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Exercise claims settlement authority as specified in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this regulation, to include appellate authority where so 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
delegated. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Designate area claims offices and grant claims settlement authority thereto. A grant of such authority will not
be effective until coordinated with the Commander, USARCS and an office code assigned. However, the chief of a command
claims 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
service may redesignate a claims processing office already having an assigned office code as an area claims office
without coordination with the Commander, USARCS. The Commander, USARCS will be informed of such a designation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Designate claims processing offices and grant claims approval authority thereto. Only claims processing offices
staffed with a JA or claims attorney may be granted approval authority. A grant of such authority will not be effective
until coordinated with the Commander, USARCS and an office code assigned. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Train claims personnel and monitor their activities. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Implement pertinent claims policies. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Prepare and publish command claims directives. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Administer the command claims expenditure allowance, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
providing necessary data, estimates, and reports to USARCS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) Perform the responsibilities of an area claims office (see paragraph (d) of this section), as applicable. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) Serve as the U.S. sending State office, if so designated, when operating in an area covered by a status of forces
agreement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Heads of area claims offices. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Heads of area claims offices will_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Ensure that claims in their area of responsibility are promptly investigated according to this regulation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Ensure that each organization or activity (for example, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
U.S. Army Reserve (USAR) or Army National Guard (ARNG) unit, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Reserve Officers' Training Corps (ROTC) detachment, recruiting 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
company or station, and DOD agency) within the area appoints a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
claims officer to investigate claims incidents not requiring 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
investigation by a JA (&sect;536.16(c)(2)) and ensure that this officer is adequately trained. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Act as a claims settlement authority on claims within 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the monetary jurisdictions set forth in this regulation and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
forward claims beyond such jurisdictions to the Commander, USARCS or to the chief of a command claims service, as appropriate,
for action. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Designate claims processing offices and request the Commander, USARCS or the chief of a command claims service,
as appropriate, to grant claims approval authority to a claims processing office with respect to claims within that
office's jurisdiction, as specified under paragraphs (b)(4) and (c)(2), of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Prepare and publish a claims directive concerning the investigation and processing of claims matters for the
guidance of all claims processing offices within their area. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
