<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(6) Implement claims policies and guidance furnished by TAJAG or Commander, USARCS through policy directives or
the Claims Manual and establish and implement necessary claims policies and procedures not contrary to the foregoing.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Ensure that there are an adequate number of qualified JAs or claims attorneys, claims examiners, claims adjudicators
and claims clerks in all claims offices within their area to take prompt action on claims and that they are adequately
trained. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) Budget and fund for claims investigations and activities to include per diem and transportation of claims personnel,
claimants and witnesses, independent medical examinations, appraisals, independent expert opinions, long distance
phone calls, recording and photographic equipment, use of express mail or couriers, and other necessary expenses.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) Within continental United States (CONUS), procure and disseminate adequate legal publications on local law
and verdicts relating to tort claims within the area of jurisdiction. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) Notify Commander, USARCS of all claims and claims incidents as required by &sect;536.17 and &sect;536.21(b)(2).

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) Develop and maintain written plans for a disaster or civil disturbance. The plan should include a requirement
for an advance party to assess the need for the presence of a special 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
claims processing office. The plans may be internal Office of the SJA plans or an annex to an installation/organizational
plan. (See also &sect;536.8(c)(4)(iii).) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(12) Implement the Army's Article 139 claims program. (See &sect;536.142.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Heads of claims processing offices. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Heads of claims processing offices will_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Investigate all potential and actual claims arising within its assigned jurisdiction, either on an area basis
or on a command or agency basis. Only a claims processing office with approval authority can adjudicate and pay all
presented claims within its monetary jurisdiction. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Ensure that units and organizations within its jurisdiction have appointed claims officers for the investigation
of claims not requiring investigation by a JA. (See &sect;536.16.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Budget and fund for claims investigations and activities to include per diem and transportation of claims personnel,
claimants and witnesses, independent medical examinations, appraisals, independent expert opinions, long distance
phone calls, recording and photographic equipment, use of express mail or couriers, and other necessary expenses.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Within CONUS, procure and maintain legal publications on local law and verdicts relating to tort claims within
their jurisdiction. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Notify the Commander, USARCS of all claims and claims incidents as required by &sect;536.17 and &sect;536.21(b)(2).

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Implement the Army's Article 139 claims program. (See &sect;536.142.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Chief of Engineers. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The COE, through the Chief Counsel, will_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Provide general supervision of the claims activities of engineer area claims offices. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Ensure that each engineer area claims office has a claims attorney designated by the Commander, USARCS, as prescribed
in &sect;536.6. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Ensure the training of claims personnel and the continuing inspection of their activities. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Provide for implementation of pertinent claims policies. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Provide for budgeting in accordance with existing Army regulations and command directives for temporary duty
(TDY), long distance phone calls, recording equipment, cameras, and other expenses for investigation and processing
of claims. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Take action to procure and have available adequate legal publications on local law relating to claims arising
within the United States, its territories, and possessions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Commanding General, U.S. Army Health Services Command (CG, HSC). 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The CG, HSC will, through his SJA, ensure that adequate and qualified medical claims JAs and medical claims investigators
are assigned for the investigation and processing of medical malpractice claims arising at Army medical centers
under his or her control. In accordance with an agreement between TJAG and The Surgeon General, such personnel will
be used primarily in investigating and processing of medical malpractice claims and provided with the necessary
funding and research materials to carry out this function. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Chief, National Guard Bureau (NGB). 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Chief, NGB will_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Ensure that a point of contact for claims matters is designated in each adjutant general office. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
