(1) If the claim is of a type and amount within the jurisdiction of the claims office of the command concerned and the
claim is meritorious in the amount claimed, it will be approved and paid. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If a claim in an amount in excess of the monetary jurisdiction of the claims office is meritorious in a lesser amount
within its jurisdiction, the claim may be approved for payment provided the amount offered is accepted by the claimant
in settlement of the claim. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If the claim is not of a type within the jurisdiction of the claims office, or if the claimant will not accept an amount
within its jurisdiction, the claim with supporting papers and a recommendation for appropriate action will be forwarded
to the next higher claims authority. Any personnel claim forwarded to a higher authority for settlement will be accompanied
by a memorandum of opinion. Prior to forwarding any tort claim, the USARCS AAO must be consulted and a joint decision
reached on whether a memorandum of opinion must be submitted. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) If the claim is determined to be not meritorious, it will be disapproved provided the claims office has settlement
authority for claims of the type and amount involved. If the type and amount of the claim requires denial by a higher
authority, the claim will be forwarded through claims channels to the appropriate authority accompanied by a claims
memorandum of opinion recommending denial. Prior to the disapproval of a claim under a particular statute, a careful
review should be made to ensure that the claim is not properly payable under a different statute or on another basis.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Claims within the exclusive jurisdiction of USARCS. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Authority to settle the type of claims listed below has not been delegated below USARCS. Command claims services or
area claims offices receiving these types of claims will investigate them in accordance with this regulation and
guidance from USARCS. Regardless of the amount claimed, a mirror copy of the claims will be sent to Tort Claims Division,
USARCS immediately on receipt. Once the investigation is complete, the files on these claims should be forwarded
directly to USARCS with a memorandum of opinion recommending disposition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Claims arising in the United States out of the actions of members of the force or civilian component of a NATO nation
or headquarters (subpart G, statutory authority). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Maritime claims for or against the Army other than those arising overseas within the jurisdiction of a command
claims service or those within the jurisdiction of Corps of Engineers and other specially designated claims offices
( See subpart H). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Claims based on the denial of a security clearance by the government to civilian employee of defense contractors
(DODD 5220.6, section 10, paragraph C). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Claims by the U.S. Postal Service against the Military Postal Service Agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) In areas where the FTCA is applicable, any claim except those under chapter 11, arising out of an accident involving
a POV driven by a member of the Army, or by ARNG personnel as defined in chapter 6, based on an allegation that the POV travel
was within the scope of employment. On these claims the memorandum of opinion will include a specific discussion on
the issue of scope of employment under applicable law (See chapters 4 and 5, AR 27&hyph;40). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Mirror file requirement. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In addition to the claims listed in &sect;536.21, USARCS is responsible for monitoring the investigation and settling
the following claims. A copy of these claims and of any claims listed in paragraph (c) of this section, will be forwarded
immediately on receipt to the Commander, USARCS, ATTN: JACS-TCD . 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A case that must be brought to the attention of the Department of Justice in accordance with The Attorney General's
Regulations (DA Pam 27&hyph;162, appendix H). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Any FTCA, MCA, or other tort claim in which the amount claimed exceeds $25,000. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) FTCA, MCA or other tort claims arising out of an incident if the combined amounts of the claims exceed $25,000. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) A claim within the exclusive jurisdiction of USARCS (see paragraph (c) of this section). The field claims office
will provide USARCS duplicates of all correspondence, records and documents relevant to the investigation and processing
of the claim as they are added to the file. Direct liaison and correspondence between USARCS and the field claims authority
is authorized and encouraged on these and all claims. In addition, heads of area claims offices in CONUS will advise
the action officer at Tort Claims Division, USARCS who is responsible for their geographic area of all potential claims
likely to meet the criteria in this paragraph or in paragraph (c) of this section, and will forward a copy of the investigation
file to USARCS on request. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
By higher settlement authority. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A higher claims settlement authority may take action with respect to a claim in the same manner as the initial claims
office. However, if it is determined that any further attempt to settle the claim would be unwarranted, the claim will
be forwarded to the Commander, USARCS, with recommendations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Claims not cognizable under subparts C through L. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If a claim is determined not to be cognizable under this regulation, reference to DA Pam 27&hyph;162, chapter 8 may
reveal a basis for compensation or consideration by another agency. If so, the claimant will be so advised. If, after
investigation, it appears that the claim may not be settled under any law or regulation, the claim, the related file,
and a memorandum of opinion will be forwarded through claim channels to the Commander, USARCS. 
