(2) There exists an immediate need of the person who suffered an injury, damage, or loss, or of the family of a person
who was killed for food, clothing, shelter, medical, burial expenses, other necessities, or other resources for
such expenses that are not reasonably available. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
