<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Written report by the attending physician or dentist setting forth the_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Nature and extent of injury. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Nature and extent of treatment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Degree of temporary or permanent disability. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Prognosis. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Period of hospitalization. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) Diminished earning capacity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Itemized bills or receipts for medical, dental, and hospital expenses. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If the prognosis includes future treatment, a statement of expected expenses for such treatment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) If the claim includes lost time from employment, a statement by the employer showing the actual time lost and wages
and/or salary lost. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) If the claim includes lost income by a self-employed claimant, documentary evidence of such loss. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.58 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Measure of damages in injury or death claims arising in foreign countries. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Where a claim for an injury, or injury resulting in death, arises outside of the United States or its possessions,
the elements of damages payable under this subpart will be the same as those payable in a similar claim arising under
the law of the District of Columbia applicable to torts committed in and having their operative effect in the District
of Columbia. The amount paid will be based on generally accepted economic principles. All awards for future payments
of economic damages will be discounted to present value. Awards under this chapter will be reduced by any benefits
which have been or are reasonably likely to be paid, if the benefit or payment is from the general revenues of the United
States and the claimant did not contribute to or purchase the benefit. In death cases, taxes and personal consumption
will be deducted from any award for lost economic contribution or lost earnings. Punitive or exemplary damages, including
damages considered punitive in nature under 28 U.S.C. 2674, and interest on any settlement are not payable. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The information listed in &sect;536.57 (b) or (c), as appropriate, will be submitted by the claimant to substantiate
a claim. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) A claimant who alleges a serious personal injury resulting in temporary or permanent disability should be examined
by an independent physician or other medical specialist. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
purpose of the examination is not just to confirm the impairment but also to help assess its extent, prognosis and treatment.
See &sect;536.27 for independent medical examination procedures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.59 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Failure to substantiate a claim. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Government is not obligated to take final action on a claim until it has been supported by the claimant with specific
facts substantiated by appropriate documentary evidence, reports of investigation, medical records, or witness
statements. As the burden of proof is on the claimant, the failure to substantiate a claim within a reasonable time
can be the basis for denial of the claim. Upon request, the claimant must_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Provide the documentation required by sections &sect;&sect;536.56 through 536.58. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Undergo necessary medical examinations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Permit questioning of the claimant, his or her witnesses, and treating medical personnel. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Submit an expert opinion in a professional negligence action. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Failure to comply with these requirements may provide a basis for denial of a claim, in full or in part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.60 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Structured settlement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The use of the structured settlement device by approval and settlement authorities is encouraged in all appropriate
cases. A structured settlement should not be used when contrary to the desires of the claimant. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Notwithstanding the above, the Commander, USARCS may require or recommend to higher authority that an acceptable
structured settlement be made a condition of award notwithstanding objection by the claimant or his or her representative
where_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Necessary to ensure adequate and secure care and compensation to a minor or otherwise incompetent claimant over
a period of years; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Where a trust device is necessary to ensure the long-term availability of funds for anticipated further medical
care; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Where the injured party's life expectancy cannot be reasonably determined. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.61 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Settlement authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
