<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (D) On duty or training with other Federal agencies, for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
example, National Aeronautics and Space Administration, DOD, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
State, Navy, or Air Force. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (E) Assigned as students or ordered into training at a non-Federal civilian educational institution, hospital,
factory, or other industry. (This does not include members on excess leave.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (F) On full-time duty at nonappropriated fund activities. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (G) Of the USAR and ARNG on active duty under Title 10. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (ii) Members of Reserve Units (other than members of the ARNG under subpart F) during periods of inactive duty training
and active duty training, including ROTC cadets who are reservists while they are at summer camp. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (iii) Members of the ARNG while engaged in training or duty under Title 32 U.S.C. sections 316, 502, 503, 504, or 505
for claims arising on or after 29 December 1981. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (2) Civilian officials and employees of both the DOD and DA (there is no practical significance to the distinction
between the terms ``official'' and ``employee'') including but not limited to_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (i) Civil Service and other full-time employees of both the DOD and DA paid from appropriated funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
