under subpart L as a matter of policy, even when the user is not within the scope of employment and the claim is not otherwise
cognizable under any of the other authorizations in this regulation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (iv) Prisoners of war and interned enemy aliens. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (v) Civilian employees of the District of Columbia National Guard, including those paid under ``service contracts''
from District of Columbia funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (vi) Civilians serving as ROTC instructors paid from Federal funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

