<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Claims that appear to be of a type that must be brought to the attention of the Attorney General in accordance with
his or her regulations (28 CFR 14.6). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) A claim in which the demand exceeds $25,000 or the total amount of all claims, actual or potential, from a single
incident exceeds $25,000 $50,000.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) USARCS is responsible for the monitoring and settlement of such claims and will be kept informed of the status of
the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
investigation and processing thereof. Direct liaison and correspondence between USARCS and the field claims authority
or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
investigator is authorized on all claims matters and assistance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
will be furnished as required. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) Non-Army claims. Claims based on acts or omissions of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
employees of the United States, other than military and civilian personnel of the DA, civilian personnel of the DOD,
and employees of nonappropriated fund activities of the DA will be transmitted forthwith to the nearest official
of the employing agency; the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
claimant will be advised of the referral. (See &sect;536.18 (c) and (d) for further guidance when more than one Federal
