receipt that a claim filed under the FTCA is not cognizable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
thereunder; for example, it is a maritime claim under chapter 8, or it falls under subparts C or F, the acknowledgment
will 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
contain a statement advising the claimant of the statute under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
which his or her claim will be processed. If it is not clear 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
which subpart applies, a statement to that effect will be made and the claimant will be promptly advised when a decision
