<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
tentative settlement can be reached for any amount, but that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
awards in excess of $200,000 are subject to approval by the Attorney General. The claimant should be advised that administrative
filing of the claim protects him or her under the statute of limitations for purpose of litigation and that a suit can
be filed within 6 months after the date of mailing of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
notice of final denial by the DA, thus potentially allowing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
negotiations to continue indefinitely. An attorney representing a claimant should be advised of the limitations
on fees for purposes of administrative settlement (20 percent) and litigation (25 percent) and that there is no jury
