<!-- PJG ITAG l=56 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart E_Claims Involving Government Vehicles and Property Not Cognizable Under Other Law 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.83 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Statutory authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The statutory authority for this subpart is contained in the act of 9 October 1962 (76 Stat. 767, 10 U.S.C 2737). This
statute is commonly called the ``Nonscope Claims Act.'' For the purposes of this subpart, a Government installation
is a facility having fixed boundaries owned or controlled by the Government, and a vehicle includes every description
of carriage or other artificial contrivance used, or capable of being used, as a means of transportation on land (1
U.S.C 4). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.84 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Scope. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) This subpart prescribes the substantive bases and special procedural requirements for the administrative settlement
and payment, in an amount not more than $1,000, of any claim against the United States not cognizable under any other
provision of law for damage or loss of property, or for personal injury or death caused by a member or employee of the
DA incident to the use of a U.S. vehicle at any location or incident to the use of other U.S. property on a Government installation.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Any claim in which there appears to be a disputed issue relating to whether the employee was acting within the scope
of employment will be considered under subparts C, D, and F of this part. Only when all parties, to include an insurer,
agree that there is no ``in scope'' issue will this chapter be used. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.85 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Claims payable. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) General. A claim for personal injury, death, or damage or loss of property, real or personal, is payable under this
chapter when_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Caused by the act or omission, negligent, wrongful, or otherwise involving fault of a member of the DA or the ARNG,
or a civilian employee of the DA or the ARNG_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Incident to the use of a vehicle of the United States at any place. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Incident to the use of any other property of the United States on a Government installation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The claim may not be settled under any other claims statute and claims regulation available to the DA for the administrative
settlement of claims. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The claim has been determined to be meritorious, and the approval or settlement authority has obtained a settlement
agreement in an amount not in excess of $1,000 in full satisfaction of the claim prior to approval of the claim for payment.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
