claimant will be required to exhaust his or her remedy against the State or its insurer, or whether the claim against
the United States can be settled without such requirement. If the Commander, USARCS, determines to follow the latter
course of action, he or she will also determine whether an assignment of the claim against the State or its insurer will
be obtained and whether recovery action will be taken. The State or its insurer will be given appropriate notification
in accordance with State law necessary to obtain contribution of indemnification. 
