<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.100 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Claims against the ARNG tortfeasor individually. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The procedures set forth in &sect;536.29 are applicable. With respect to claims arising before 29 December 1981,
an ARNG driver acting pursuant to the authorities cited in &sect;536.94(a) is not protected by the provisions of the
Drivers Act (28 U.S.C. 2670(b)); the driver may be sued individually in State court. When this situation occurs, it
should be monitored closely by ARNG authorities. If possible an early determination will be made as to whether any
private insurance of the ARNG tortfeasor is applicable. Where such insurance is applicable and the claim against
the United States is doubtful validity, final actions will be withheld pending resolution of the demand against the
NG tortfeasor. If, in the opinion of the claims approving or settlement authority, such insurance is applicable and
the claim against the United States is payable in full or in a reduced amount, settlement efforts will be made either
together with the insurer or singly by the United States as in &sect;536.99(b). Any settlement will not include amounts
recovered or recoverable as in &sect;536.28. If the insurance is not applicable, settlement or disapproval action
will proceed without further delay. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.101 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
When claims must be presented. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A claim may be settled under this subpart only if presented in writing within 2 years after it accrues, except that if
it accrues in time of war or armed conflict, or if war or armed conflict intervenes within 2 years after it accrues, and
if good cause is shown, the claim may be presented not later than 2 years after war or armed conflict is terminated. As
used in this paragraph, war or armed conflict is one in which any Armed Force of the United States is engaged. The dates
of commencement and termination of an armed conflict must be established by concurrent resolution of Congress or
by determination of the President. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.102 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Where claims must be presented. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A claim must be presented to the appropriate Federal agency. Presentment of a written claim to any full time officer
or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
employee of the NG will be considered a receipt. However, the statute of limitations is tolled if a claim is filed with
a State agency, the claim purports to be under the NGCA and it is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
forwarded to the Army within 6 months, or the claimant makes 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
inquiry of the Army concerning the claim within 6 months. If a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
claim is received by a DA official who is not a claims approval or settlement authority under this regulation, the claim
will be transmitted without delay to the nearest approval or settlement 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.103 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Procedures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The form of a claim under this Act will be as described in &sect;536.20 (d) and (e). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) So far as they are not inconsistent with this subpart, the procedures set forth in subpart B, settlement procedures,
will be followed in processing a claim under this subpart. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The following provisions of subpart C are applicable to claims under this subpart and are hereby incorporated
by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
following references: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Applicable law (&sect;536.55). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Determination of quantum (&sect;536.56 through section 536.59 ). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Delegation of authority (&sect;536.61). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Claims over $100,000 (&sect;536.62). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Settlement procedures (&sect;537.63). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Action on appeal (&sect;536.64). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Attorney fees (&sect;536.66). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.104. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Settlement agreement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Procedures concerning settlement agreements will be in accordance with &sect;536.32, except that the agreement
will be modified to include a State and its NG in most cases. A copy of the agreement will be furnished to State authorities
and the individual tortfeasor. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=56 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart G_Claims Under Status of Forces and Other International Agreements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
General 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.105 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Statutory Authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The authority for this subpart is contained in the following:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 10 U.S.C. 2734a as amended, concerning claims arising overseas under international agreements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 10 U.S.C. 2734b, as amended, concerning claims arising under international agreements in this country. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 10 U.S.C. 2735 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 10 U.S.C. 2736, as amended, providing for advance payment of certain claims. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
Claims Arising in the United States 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.106
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Scope.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) This subpart provides procedures and defines responsibilities for the investigation, processing, and settlement
of claims arising out of acts or omissions of members of a foreign military force or civilian component present in the
United States, or a territory, commonwealth, or possession thereof under the provisions of reciprocal international
agreements, which contain claims settlement provisions applicable to claims arising in the United States, such
as Article VIII of the Agreement Regarding the Status of Forces of Parties to the North Atlantic Treaty (DA Pam 27&hyph;162,
appendix L). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

