<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.194 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Claims arising from intra-theater shipments. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Unless private insurance or payment of the statutory limit is involved (see &sect;536.190)_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Recovery action under a European intra-theater tender or a delivering direct procurement method contract will
be assembled and forwarded to U.S. Army Claims Service, Europe, APO AE 09166&hyph;5346. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Recovery action under a Korean intra-theater tender or a delivering direct procurement method contract will
be assembled and forwarded to U.S. Armed Forces Claims Service, Korea, APO SF 96301 AP 96205&hyph;0084. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Other recovery action against a delivering third party not involving shipment under a Through Government Bill
of Lading will be processed by the field claims office to completion in accordance with DA Pam 27&hyph;162, chapter
3. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.195 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Claims against ocean carriers. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
No demand will be made directly on an ocean carrier operating under a Military Sealift Command contract by individual
claimants or by field claims offices. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
POVs
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Payment less than $100.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 A POV shipment file will be closed and no recovery action taken when the amount paid for the damage is less than $100.
However any file involving loss of items from vehicles will continue to be processed regardless of the amount paid.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Payment from $100&hyph;1,999.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For POV claims paid for any amount between $100 and $1,999, and if there is evidence of ocean carrier liability, the
entire claim file will be forwarded to Military Sealift Command, Atlantic, by transmittal letter prepared in the
format shown in DA Pam 27&hyph;162, figure 3&hyph;18. However, if there is evidence of liability attributable to
the inland shipment of POVs in Europe, the entire claim file will instead be forwarded to the U.S. Army Claims Service,
Europe, ATTN: AEUTN&hyph;PCR, APO AE 09166&hyph;5346. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Payment $2,000 or more
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Non-European claims offices.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If the amount paid on a POV shipment claim is $2,000 or more, or if it appears that the POV was dropped or was mishandled
severely in shipment, claims personnel will prioritize recovery action and handle the larger claims first. Claims
personnel will_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Assert a demand against the responsible contractor if an outport contractor, stevedore, or inland transporter
damaged the vehicle; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Forward the claim to USACSEUR for recovery if the damage occurred while the POV was in the custody of a European outport,
stevedore, or inland shipment contractor; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Close the file and forward it for retirement if the POV was damaged while in the custody of government personnel;
or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) Forward the claim to the Military Sealift Command if the damage occurred while the vehicle was in the custody of
the ocean carrier (ship) or if claims personnel cannot determine where the damage occurred. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
European claims offices.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If the amount paid on a POV shipment claim is $2,000 or more, claims personnel will prioritize assembly of the file and
will forward it to USACSEUR for recovery action 21 days after the claim is paid. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Personal property other than vehicles (for example, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
household goods).
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 After payment of a claim involving personal property other than POV's, the entire claim file will be forwarded, in
duplicate, directly to the Commander, USARCS, for recovery action as appropriate. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.196 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Centralized recovery program procedures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
After settlement of a claim under this chapter (including direct procurement method (DPM) or intra-theater shipments
(only if private insurance is involved), and all mobile home claims), requiring centralized recovery processing
as determined by the Commander, USARCS, the office paying the claim will forward the file to USARCS within 30 days.
(See also &sect;536.184(a)(6).) All such claims where recovery action is anticipated will include legible documentation
and will be assembled as described below. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) The following documents will be affixed to the left inside cover (opposite the side bearing complete name and file
number of claimant) in descending order: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
First.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 An unsealed envelope addressed to the appropriate third party along with the demand packet which should include the
following documents: (i) Original DD Form 1843 (Demand on Carrier/Contractor). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(See DA Pam 27&hyph;162, paragraph 3&hyph;20.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Copy of DD Form 1164 (Service Order for Personal 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Property) if applicable. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Copy of DD Form 1844. (See DA Pam 27&hyph;162, paragraph 3&hyph;19.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Copy of DD Form 1841 (Government Inspection Report) if available. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Copies of all repair estimates. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) Copies of all other supporting documents deemed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
appropriate. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) Copy of DD Form 1840/1840R. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Second.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If applicable, an unearned freight packet 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consisting of the original letter requesting deduction of unearned freight charges with a copy of the GBL, DD Form
1843, and DD Form 1844 attached thereto. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Third.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Copy of DD Form 1843. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Fourth.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If applicable, GBL and/or DD Form 1164. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Fifth.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Documents of timely notice as described in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section 536.188(c). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Sixth.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 DD Form 1844. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Seventh.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
