<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;536.213 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Federal statutory authority. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The Federal Claims Collection Act (31 U.S.C. 3711), as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amended by the Debt Collection Act of 1982 and Public Law 101&hyph;552 (15 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
November 1990). The Federal Claims Collection Act states that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal agencies will try to collect all claims of the United 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
States for money or property. Among other things, it provides a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
basis for agencies to recover for damage to Government property. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Federal Medical Care Recovery Act (42 U.S.C. 2651&hyph;53) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(hereinafter ``FMCRA''). The FMCRA provides for the recovery of the reasonable value of medical care furnished by
the United 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
States on account of injury or disease incurred under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
circumstances creating tort liability upon some third person. The FMCRA is implemented by Executive Order 11060
and 28 CFR part 43; the Federal Claims Collection Standards (DA Pam 27&hyph;162, appendix M) also apply, as appropriate.
However, some procedures appropriate for liquidated debts may not be appropriate for unliquidated claims. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 10 U.S.C. 1095. 10 U.S.C. 1095 provides authority for military health care facilities to collect the reasonable
cost of health care from health insurance and medicare supplemental policies. As amended by Public Law 101&hyph;510
(5 November 1990), this statute provides claims offices with additional authority to assert claims against automobile
insurers for care provided in an MTF on or after that date. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Other authority. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) State Workers' Compensation laws. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) State hospital lien laws. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Contract rights under terms of insurance policies 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
including medical payment coverage, uninsured and underinsured 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
coverages, and no-fault. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) State automobile no-fault laws. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
