<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

</FOOTNAME>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
Short positioning municipal securities is rare because the Internal Revenue Service will not allow both a borrower
and lender of a municipal security to claim a tax exemption. In effect, the lender of a municipal security would be trading
tax exempt interest for taxable interest. In addition, to the extent that any short positioning occurs with respect
to municipal securities, the IRS imposes additional reporting requirements on the participating parties. 
