disclosure requirements for asset backed securities. On the one hand, the Commission proposes to expand the range
of debt securities where yield need not be disclosed to include any asset backed security subject to continuous prepayment.
<FOOTCITE>44</FOOTCITE>
 Broker-dealers must disclose yield information with respect to debt instruments that are insulated from prepayment
risk, or where sufficient certainty exists to permit an accurate forecast of the yield that investors will receive.
