<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
6. Preliminary Note to Rule 10b&hyph;10 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Commission proposes to add a preliminary note to Rule 10b&hyph;10 to clarify the relationship between the Rule's
disclosure requirements and additional disclosures that may be required to satisfy antifraud provisions of the
federal securities laws. In several cases over the years, broker-dealer defendants have argued that because Rule
10b&hyph;10 did not require disclosure of specific information on a confirmation, it was not material for purposes
of the general antifraud provisions of the Exchange Act.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
46
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Although courts have given short shrift to these arguments, the Commission wishes to reiterate that Rule 10b&hyph;10
is not a safe harbor from the general antifraud provisions of the federal securities laws.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
47
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 A broker-dealer has a duty established by federal common law theories
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
48
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 independent of the requirements of Rule 10b&hyph;10 to disclose material facts to an investor at the time of the investor's
investment decision.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
49
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 
