<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
This section requires broker-dealers to disclose specified information in writing to customers at or before the
completion of a transaction. The requirements under this section that particular information be disclosed is not
determinative of a broker-dealer's obligation under the general antifraud provisions of the federal securities
laws to disclose additional information to a customer at the time of the customer's investment decision.
