<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Director will periodically review the list of captive-bred exotic bird species in &sect;15.33(a), for which
importation into the United States is approved. Any exotic bird species listed in paragraph 15.33(a) pursuant to
this section must meet all of the following criteria: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) All specimens of the species known to be in trade (legal or illegal) are captive-bred; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) No specimens of the species are known to be removed from the wild for the pet bird market; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Any importation of specimens of the species would not be detrimental to the survival of the species in the wild;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Adequate enforcement controls are in place in countries of export to ensure compliance with paragraphs (a) through
(c) of this section. 
